1. Deposit money
Validation goes on API side, check frontend-backend integration.

1.1 Positive ->
PRECONDITIONS
Step 1: Admin logs in
Step 2: Admin creates user
Step 3: User logs in
Step 4: User creates account
TEST
Step 5: User deposits money (random value from 1 to 5000)
CHECK
Step 6: UI alert -> Successfully deposited $sum to account accountName! + check deposit is in the transactions history
Step 7: Backend check: confirms the money was deposited.

1.2 Negative (Invalid Amount) ->
PRECONDITIONS
Step 1: Admin logs in
Step 2: Admin creates user
Step 3: User logs in
Step 4: User creates account
TEST
Step 5: User attempts to deposit an invalid amount (random 0, negative and greater than 5000)
CHECK
Step 6: UI alert -> Please deposit less or equal to 5000$. + check deposit is not in the transactions history
Step 7: Backend check: confirms the money was not deposited

1.3 Negative (No Account Selected) ->
PRECONDITIONS
Step 1: Admin logs in
Step 2: Admin creates user
Step 3: User logs in
TEST
Step 4: User attempts to deposit money (random value from 1 to 5000) without selecting an account.
CHECK
Step 5: UI alert -> Please select an account. + check deposit is not in the transactions history
Step 6: Backend check: confirms the money was not deposited.


2. Transfer money
Validation goes on API side, check frontend-backend integration

2.1 Positive ->
PRECONDITIONS
Step 1: Admin logs in
Step 2: Admin creates user
Step 3: User logs in
Step 4: User creates account1
Step 5: User deposits money into account1
Step 6: User creates account2
TEST
Step 7: User transfers money (random value from 1 to 10000) from account1 to account2
CHECK
Step 8: UI alert -> Successfully transferred $sum to account accountNumber! + check transfer is in the transactions history
Step 9: Backend check: confirms the money was transferred, balance account1 = initial balance on account 1 - transfer amount,
balance account2 = initial balance on account 2 + transfer amount.

2.2 Negative (Invalid Amount) ->
PRECONDITIONS
Step 1: Admin logs in
Step 2: Admin creates user
Step 3: User logs in
Step 4: User creates account1
Step 5: User deposits money into account1
Step 6: User creates account2
TEST
Step 7: User attempts to transfer an invalid amount (e.g., 0, a negative number, or more than 10000).
CHECK
Step 8: UI alert ->  Error: Transfer amount must be ... + The transfer is NOT visible in the transaction history.
Step 9: Backend check: confirms the money was not transferred, balances on the accounts were not changed

2.3 Negative (Missing Confirmation) ->
PRECONDITIONS
Step 1: Admin logs in
Step 2: Admin creates user
Step 3: User logs in
Step 4: User creates account1
Step 5: User deposits money on account1
Step 6: User creates account2
TEST
Step 7: User fills in transfer details (random value from 1 to 10000) but leaves the confirmation checkbox unchecked
CHECK
Step 8: UI alert -> Please fill all fields and confirm. + check transfer is not in the transactions history
Step 9: Backend check: confirms the money was not transferred, balances on the accounts were not changed


